Carousel is a simple jQuery plugin to cycle through a list of elements.

Here's a quick example:

    <style>
        li { display: none; }
        .active { display: block; }
    </style>

    <ul>
        <li>Item 1</li>
        <li>Item 2</li>
        <li>Item 3</li>
        <li>Item 4</li>
    </ul>
    <a class="prev" href="#">Prev</a> / <a class="next" href="#">Next</a>

    <script>
        $(function() {
            $("li").carousel({
                next: $(".next"),
                prev: $(".prev")
            });
        });
    </script>
